title: Spicy Chicken Jerky in the Air Fryer

Ingredients.1: 2 (5 ounce) boneless chicken breasts, cut into strips

Ingredients.2: 0.5 cup mojo criollo marinade (such as Goya®)

Directions.1: Combine chicken strips, marinade, and Cajun seasoning in a resealable plastic bag. Refrigerate for 8 hours to overnight.

Directions.2: Measure skewers to fit across the air fryer basket, slightly overlapping the edge. Trim off excess length.

Directions.3: Preheat the air fryer to 180 degrees F (80 degrees C) for 10 minutes.

Directions.4: Thread chicken strips onto skewers, leaving room in between each strip, while the air fryer is preheating.

Directions.5: Air fry for 1 hour 15 minutes. Adjust cooking time as most air fryers have a maximum setting of 30 minutes. Rearrange the skewers during the reset time.

Directions.6: Increase temperature to 200 degrees F (95 degrees C) and air fry for an additional 15 minutes.

Directions.7: Remove strips to a paper towel-lined storage container. Seal. Allow to rest overnight before serving.
